STOP DB2:

STOP HADR (IF EXIST)
db2 stop hadr on db DBNAME
db2 connect to DBNAME
db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all;db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all;db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all; db2 force application all;
db2 deactivate db DBNAME;
db2 terminate

START DB2

STOP HADR (IF EXIST)
db2 start hadr on db DBNAME as standby

db2start
db2 activate db DBNAME
db2 connect to DBNAME

db2 list applications;
